---
import LegalPage from "../components/LegalPage.astro";
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { SITE } from "../lib/site";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Use - VivyShot"
  description="Terms of Use for VivyShot, a macOS screenshot capture and editing app by Vivy Technologies Co., Limited."
  canonicalPath="/terms"
  ogType="article"
>
  <LegalPage title="Terms of Use" lastUpdated="April 5, 2026">
    <section>
      <h2>1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
      <p>
        By downloading, installing, or using VivyShot ("the App"), you agree to these Terms of Use. If
        you do not agree, do not use the App.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>2. Product Scope</h2>
      <p>
        VivyShot is being developed as a screenshot capture and editing product with a Rust-first core.
        The currently supported official app surface is macOS.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>3. Licensing</h2>
      <p>
        Source code published at <a href={SITE.githubUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">{SITE.githubUrl}</a>
        {" "}uses a split licensing model.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>The Rust core and generated FFI header are licensed under MIT.</li>
        <li>The macOS app sources are licensed under GPL-3.0-only.</li>
        <li>Official App Store binaries use Apple’s App Store terms together with VivyShot binary terms.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>4. Restrictions</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>You may not use the App for unlawful purposes.</li>
        <li>You may not remove or alter proprietary notices in official binaries.</li>
        <li>You may not misrepresent modified builds as official VivyShot releases.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>5. Captured Content</h2>
      <p>
        You are responsible for the content you capture, annotate, export, and share through VivyShot,
        including ensuring you have permission to capture or distribute that material.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>6. App Store Distribution</h2>
      <p>
        Official macOS distribution is expected through Apple’s App Store. Pricing and tiers may change
        over time and are not finalized today. If the App is purchased through Apple, billing and
        account management are handled by Apple.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>7. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
      <p>
        THE APP IS PROVIDED "AS IS" WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED. WE DO NOT WARRANT
        THAT THE APP WILL BE UNINTERRUPTED, ERROR-FREE, OR SUITABLE FOR EVERY WORKFLOW.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>8. Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p>
        IN NO EVENT SHALL VIVY TECHNOLOGIES CO., LIMITED BE LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL,
        SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES ARISING OUT OF YOUR USE OF THE APP OR WEBSITE.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>9. Governing Law</h2>
      <p>
        These terms shall be governed by the laws of Hong Kong SAR, without regard to its conflict of
        law provisions.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>10. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For questions about these Terms, contact <a href="mailto:vivyshot@vivy.company">vivyshot@vivy.company</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </LegalPage>
</BaseLayout>
